    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arco</ex></expan> Agrippae <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> II</supplied>I <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">tr</supplied>ib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>potest</abbr><ex>ate</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">VI</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> Iulius regis</supplied> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">Donni <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Cottius</supplied> <lb n="6"/>Don<supplied reason="lost">nu</supplied>s et Cotti<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">us</supplied> <lb n="7"/>Cotti <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilii</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die Inschrift wurde zusammen mit Teilen einer vergoldeten Bronzestatue des Agrippa gefunden. Marmor, weiß. Statuenbasis? Platte? (B): Z. 4: Ferrua: [--- M. Iulius Cottius]; Letta, Rosso: [vi C. M. (?) Iulii] Z. 6: Ferrero: Do[nni] et Cotti(i) vel Do[nnus] et Cott(i); AE 1905, p. 14 s. n. 48: Do [nnu]s et Cotti(i); Ferrua: Donnus et Cottiu[us]; Letta: Don[nu]s et Cotti[us]; Rosso: Donn[u]s et Cotti[us].</p>
            </div>
